The spec covers the full mistake review experience based on the current codebase analysis:

- **Current UX/UI problems** — 14 issues identified from the existing `Mistakes.tsx` and `MistakeNotebook.tsx` implementations (flat list, no pattern detection, no AI integration, manual status transitions, no practice connection)
- **Proposed three-section layout** — Overview dashboard (summary cards + skill breakdown + repeated patterns), filterable mistake list, and detail/review panel
- **Section 1: Dashboard** — Summary cards (Total/New/Reviewed/Resolved/Rate), interactive skill breakdown bar chart, repeated mistake pattern detection
- **Section 2: Mistake List** — Search, multi-dimensional filters (skill/topic/status/date/repetition), sort, batch operations, grouping by pattern
- **Section 3: Detail Panel** — Mistake/correction display, explanation, AI Tutor insight, fix recommendations, inline practice questions, mistake timeline, related mistakes
- **Daily Review workflow** — Structured one-by-one review flow with reveal and status actions
- **AI Tutor integration** — 7 entry points (insight, analysis, practice generation, pattern detection, daily review companion)
- **Design notes** — Mistakes as learning cards, pattern detection as insight, AI as mistake coach, mobile-first panel layout
